# ----------------------------------------------------
# Commit message convention (Conventional Commits)
# Format: <type>(<scope>): <short summary>
# ----------------------------------------------------
# Types:
#   feat     – new feature
#   fix      – bug fix
#   refactor – code refactoring (no behavior change)
#   chore    – config, build, deps
#   docs     – documentation / comments
#   style    – formatting, lint, prettier
#   test     – adding or updating tests
#
# Scopes (examples for your project):
#   api, routes, controller, model, db, auth, tours, users, stats
#
# Example:
#   feat(controller): add getMonthlyPlan aggregation
#   fix(model): correct price validation in Tour schema
#
# ----------------------------------------------------

<type>(<scope>): <short summary>

# Optional body (why change was made, details, notes)
# 
# BREAKING CHANGE: describe breaking API change here
